{"key":"post-19859350","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>19859350</id>\n<content>You want to sterilize at 100 kpa which is .1 mpa.&amp;nbsp; That means the needle on your gauge will only move to the second line.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The low temp figures are how much you're supposed to add to 100 C to get the temperature.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At 100 kpa or .1 mpa which is also 15 psi, you add 20 C to get a final temperature of 120 C.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Leave the vent open until all the air escapes and you have nothing but steam.&amp;nbsp; I'd still leave it cracked slightly during the process.&amp;nbsp; You only need 2 to 3 cm of water in the bottom.&amp;nbsp; Keep the jars elevated so they only get steam.&amp;nbsp; Cover the tops with foil to keep water from dripping in as condensation forms on the lid.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>19893690</next>\n<prev>19859299</prev>\n<first>19859240</first>\n<last>19893865</last>\n<when>1397754162</when>\n<utime>04/17/14 08:02 PM</utime>\n</post>"}